Holy Cross Day, the14th of September, like that of the Presentation in the Temple, is a festival of Palestinian origin. It was the anniversary of the dedication cf the basilicas erected by Constantine on the sites of Calvary and the Holy Sepulchra. This dedication festival was celebrated in 335 by the bishops attending tbe Council of Tyra, who had pronounced upon St. Athanasius the sentence of deposition. There was associated with it also the com· memoration of the discovery of the true cross.
